Comment 1: James: Traffic turning into william street from kenwick link and want to turn right into the traffic branch have to cross over traffic coming up albany Highway with very little distance to get in the right lane
Comment 2: Beatrice: When crossing Albany Hwy from Kenwick Link into William Street only two or three cars get across on a green light during the day, especially at peak hours.  This causes long lines of traffic waiting to cross, while left turning traffic passes through quickly.
Comment 3: Arun: This is the busiest intersection which takes you to the licencing centre and the shopping centre where the merging traffic and turning traffic all at one small corner.
Comment 5: Tammie: Albany Hwy traffic turning left into William St and Kenwick Link tragfic heading straight into William St --- there is alot of criss crossing of traffic as some want to go from the RH lane into the LH to turn into the driveway for Dept of Transport/Retravision, etc. Then you've got the drivers in the LH lane moving into the RH lane to turn into Spotlight, etc. Not many drivers want to give way or just barge across. Not set out very well
Comment 6: Sharon: Entering William St from Albany Hwy or Kenwick Link, it becomes very congested as converging motorists attempt to cross lanes to enter the carpark driveway into the shopping area around Retravision. Furthermore, the Licencing Centre is near Retravision, so there are many people doing driving tests in that area, which slows down motorists exiting the carpark. Would be good to have slip lane into carpark to reduce risk, or force/encourage all motorists to exit via the two Albany Hwy exits.
